@minrk the script is huge: it's a big MCMC computation.  I'm using (link: http://dan.iel.fm/emcee/) as the engine for the MCMC sampling, with a likelihood function i wrote myself.  The code spends basically all of its time in the likelihood function, which is numpy python.

I manage my python install through macports, so i believe that python.org is the original source (but please correct me if that's not the case.)

@wms2006 indeed the 'disable app nap' box was not checked, even after running the command i typed above.  I think that implies i got the wrong identifier.  I've checked it now, and will see how i go.  (The one good thing about this is that i can keep justifying walking away from my computer for a half hour as testing!)
